ce:section.ce:para:
To thoroughly investigate the practical application potential of the sensing system utilizing NCQDs, a comprehensive approach was undertaken to quantitatively and qualitatively detect Hg2+ in real samples. The real samples, which included grass shrimp, Chinese Mitten Crab, Ctenopharyngodon idella, and rice samples, were analyzed in the absence and presence of Hg2+ (0.05 and 0.10 μmol/L) using the NCQDs (Table 1
                        ). Test results showed that NCQDs could identify the spiked Hg2+ concentrations in real samples, and good recovery was obtained. To prove the accuracy of NCQDs, the spiked Hg2+ concentrations (2.5 and 8.5 μg/kg) in grass shrimp and rice samples were also analyzed using traditional methods (atomic absorption spectroscopy, GB 5009.17–2021). Table 2
                         reveals that the results obtained using these two methods are in good agreement. This finding suggested that the NCQDs quantitatively detected Hg2+ in real samples reasonably and efficiently.
